  "text": "## LLVM Loop Vectorization Infrastructure - Core Components\n\nThe LLVM loop vectorization infrastructure consists of multiple interconnected C++ components organized in the `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/` and `llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/` directories.\n\n### Five Core Files (As Required):\n\n1. **LoopVectorize.cpp** (`github.com/sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d:llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp`)\n   - Main implementation file containing the `LoopVectorizePass` pass\n   - Defines `LoopVectorizationCostModel` class (lines 882+) which determines profitable vectorization factors\n   - Also contains `InnerLoopVectorizer` class for actual instruction widening\n   - Implements the main loop vectorization logic and decision-making\n\n2. **LoopVectorize.h** (`github.com/sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d:llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.h`)\n   - Defines `LoopVectorizePass` struct (lines 131+) implementing the pass interface\n   - Defines `LoopVectorizeOptions` struct (lines 85-119) for pass configuration\n   - Header-only interface for the vectorization pass\n\n3. **LoopVectorizationLegality.h** (`github.com/sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d:llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorizationLegality.h`)\n   - Defines `LoopVectorizationLegality` class (lines 261+) that checks if a loop can be vectorized\n   - Defines `LoopVectorizeHints` class for handling loop metadata annotations\n   - Provides legality analysis infrastructure\n\n4. **LoopVectorizationLegality.cpp** (`github.com/sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d:llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorizationLegality.cpp`)\n   - Implementation of legality checks for vectorization\n   - Analyzes data dependencies, memory access patterns, and loop structure\n   - Identifies induction and reduction variables\n\n5. **VPlan.h & VPlan.cpp** (`github.com/sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d:llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.h` and `.cpp`)\n   - Defines and implements the `VPlan` class (lines 4491+ in VPlan.h, lines 873+ in VPlan.cpp)\n   - Represents a Vectorization Plan encoding decisions for vectorized loop generation\n   - Contains hierarchical CFG of VPBasicBlocks and VPRegionBlocks\n   - VPlan is the core data structure representing the vectorized loop body\n\n### Supporting Infrastructure Files:\n\n**Planner and Recipe Building:**\n- `LoopVectorizationPlanner.h` - Drives vectorization using VPlan (contains `LoopVectorizationPlanner` and `VPBuilder` classes)\n- `VPRecipeBuilder.h` - Builds instruction recipes for VPlan (`VPRecipeBuilder` class)\n\n**VPlan Utilities and Analysis:**\n- `VPlanHelpers.h` - Helper utilities and `VPLane` class for VPlan operations\n- `VPlanAnalysis.h/cpp` - Type analysis, ephemeral recipe collection, and other analyses\n- `VPlanValue.h` - VPlan value classes and value numbering\n- `VPlanCFG.h` - Control flow graph utilities for VPlan\n- `VPlanDominatorTree.h` - Dominator tree computation for VPlan\n- `VPlanPatternMatch.h` - Pattern matching utilities for VPlan recipes\n\n**VPlan Transformations:**\n- `VPlanTransforms.h/cpp` - VPlan transformation passes and optimizations (buildVPlan0, etc.)\n- `VPlanConstruction.cpp` - Initial VPlan construction from loop IR\n- `VPlanRecipes.cpp` - Implementation of various VPlan recipe types\n- `VPlanUnroll.cpp` - Loop unrolling transformations in VPlan\n- `VPlanPredicator.cpp` - Predication utilities for VPlan\n- `VPlanSLP.h/cpp` - Superword-level parallelism utilities within VPlan\n\n**Verification and Utilities:**\n- `VPlanVerifier.h/cpp` - VPlan structure verification and validation\n- `VPlanUtils.h/cpp` - General utility functions for VPlan manipulation\n\n### Architecture Summary:\n\nThe loop vectorization infrastructure works as follows:\n1. **LoopVectorizePass** initiates vectorization of a function\n2. **LoopVectorizationLegality** analyzes if each loop can be vectorized\n3. **LoopVectorizationCostModel** determines profitability and optimal vector width\n4. **LoopVectorizationPlanner** creates **VPlan** candidates using the VPlan infrastructure\n5. **VPRecipeBuilder** constructs recipes representing vectorized instructions\n6. **VPlan transformations** optimize the plan through various passes\n7. **InnerLoopVectorizer** generates final vectorized IR from the VPlan\n\nThe VPlan-based infrastructure represents the modern vectorization path enabling sophisticated transformations and outer-loop vectorization support."
}

